-a[information about processes and users]
-c[new reports below previous reports instead of overprinting them]
-C[processes or lwps that are bound to processor sets in the list]
-d[specify the representation of time]
-h[only processes or lwps whose home lgroup is in the list]
-H[information about home lgroup]
-j[only processes or lwps whose project ID is in the given list]
-J[information about processes and projects]
-k[only processes or lwps whose task ID is in tasklist]
-L[statistics for each light-weight process (LWP)]
-m[microstate process accounting information]
-n[restrict number of output lines]
-p[only processes whose process ID is in the list]
-P[only processes or lwps which have most recently executed on a CPU in the list]
-R[Put prstat in the real time scheduling class]
-s[Sort key (descending)]
-S[Sort key (ascending)]
-t[total usage summary for each user]
-T[information about processes and tasks]
-u[only processes whose effective user ID is in the list]
-U[only processes whose real user ID is in the list]
-v[verbose process usage]
-z[only processes or LWPs whose zone ID is in the list]
-Z[information about processes and zones]
